texts.html: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) — Federico Higuain scored two goals for the second straight match, lifting the Columbus Crew to a 2-0 victory over Toronto FC on Saturday night.
text: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) — Federico Higuain scored two goals for the second straight match, lifting the Columbus Crew to a 2-0 victory over Toronto FC on Saturday night.

texts.html: The Argentinean forward gave the Crew (8-11-5) the lead in the 19th minute, then for the second straight game had an exquisite chip for the second tally in the 67th. Higuain perfectly placed a looping ball from 23 yards over the futile effort of goalkeeper Joe Bendik, who was only a few yards off the goal line.
text: The Argentinean forward gave the Crew (8-11-5) the lead in the 19th minute, then for the second straight game had an exquisite chip for the second tally in the 67th. Higuain perfectly placed a looping ball from 23 yards over the futile effort of goalkeeper Joe Bendik, who was only a few yards off the goal line.

texts.html: Higuain is tied with Dominic Oduro for the team lead with nine goals as the Crew have consecutive wins for the first time since Aug. 29 and Sept. 1, 2012, a span of 32 games.
text: Higuain is tied with Dominic Oduro for the team lead with nine goals as the Crew have consecutive wins for the first time since Aug. 29 and Sept. 1, 2012, a span of 32 games.

texts.html: Toronto FC (4-12-8) has lost two straight after winning its previous two.
text: Toronto FC (4-12-8) has lost two straight after winning its previous two.

texts.html: MONTREAL (AP) — Marco Di Vaio scored twice and Montreal snapped a two game skid by beating D.C. United..
text: MONTREAL (AP) — Marco Di Vaio scored twice and Montreal snapped a two game skid by beating D.C. United..

texts.html: Montreal (11-7-5) won for the second time in its last nine matches.
text: Montreal (11-7-5) won for the second time in its last nine matches.

texts.html: Conor Doyle scored for D.C. (3-17-4), which is winless in 11 road matches while totaling just three goals.
text: Conor Doyle scored for D.C. (3-17-4), which is winless in 11 road matches while totaling just three goals.

texts.html: DiVaio got Montreal on the scoreboard in the 43rd minute. After a strong effort on the right wing, midfielder Justin Mapp crossed the ball in for Di Vaio and the striker scored his 12th goal of the season, and his first since July 3.
text: DiVaio got Montreal on the scoreboard in the 43rd minute. After a strong effort on the right wing, midfielder Justin Mapp crossed the ball in for Di Vaio and the striker scored his 12th goal of the season, and his first since July 3.

texts.html: Doyle tied the score in the 81st, and Di Vaio put Montreal back ahead in the 83rd as he converted from the left wing off a header by Patrice Bernier.
text: Doyle tied the score in the 81st, and Di Vaio put Montreal back ahead in the 83rd as he converted from the left wing off a header by Patrice Bernier.

texts.html: FOXBOROUGH, Mass. (AP) — Juan Agudelo returned to the lineup after a two-month injury absence and scored a dazzling goal in the 54th minute to lead New England over Chicago.
text: FOXBOROUGH, Mass. (AP) — Juan Agudelo returned to the lineup after a two-month injury absence and scored a dazzling goal in the 54th minute to lead New England over Chicago.

texts.html: Kelyn Rowe banged in a rebound of a Saer Sene drive in 1st minute of injury time for New England's second goal.
text: Kelyn Rowe banged in a rebound of a Saer Sene drive in 1st minute of injury time for New England's second goal.

texts.html: The 20-year old Agudelo took a long, looping pass from midfielder Chris Tierney and nudged a one-touch volley over on-charging Chicago goalie Sean Johnson.
text: The 20-year old Agudelo took a long, looping pass from midfielder Chris Tierney and nudged a one-touch volley over on-charging Chicago goalie Sean Johnson.

texts.html: New England ended a two-match winless and scoreless streak, improving to 9-9-6 on the season, 5-4-3 at home. Chicago (9-10-4) had its four-match (3-0-1) unbeaten streak end, being shut out on the road for the fifth time this season. The Fire had scored in 12 consecutive matches.

texts.html: Agudelo missed eight games recovering from a right knee sprain.

texts.html: HARRISON, N.J. (AP) — Zac MacMath came up with the big saves that allowed Philadelphia to escape with a scoreless draw against New York.
text: HARRISON, N.J. (AP) — Zac MacMath came up with the big saves that allowed Philadelphia to escape with a scoreless draw against New York.

texts.html: The goalkeeper had a strong game from beginning to end, saving Dax McCarty's point-blank header in injury time inches from the goal line.
text: The goalkeeper had a strong game from beginning to end, saving Dax McCarty's point-blank header in injury time inches from the goal line.

texts.html: Philadelphia (10-7-8) came close to giving up a winning goal in the 63rd minute, but was bailed out when MacMath leaped in front of Peguy Luyindula and grabbed Tim Cahill's header near the goalmouth. MacMath made two huge saves in the first half as well. He shares the MLS lead for clean sheets (9).

texts.html: HOUSTON (AP) — Giles Barnes scored twice in the first half and Will Bruin added a goal in the second half to lead Houston over Seattle.

texts.html: The win was the second in three games for the Dynamo (10-7-6), while Seattle (10-8-4) saw its four-game unbeaten streak end in U.S. national team captain Clint Dempsey's his first start for the Sounders.

texts.html: CARSON, Calif. (AP) — Robbie Keane scored three goals to help Los Angeles rally for a victory over Western Conference-leading Real Salt Lake.
text: CARSON, Calif. (AP) — Robbie Keane scored three goals to help Los Angeles rally for a victory over Western Conference-leading Real Salt Lake.

texts.html: Keane scored in the 56th, 67th and 86th minutes to help the Galaxy (11-9-4) pull four points behind Salt Lake and tighten an eight-team battle for five West playoff berths. The top seven teams are separated by eight points, with San Jose another three points back.

texts.html: Joao Plata gave Real Salt Lake (12-8-5) a lead in the 53rd minute.
